## SLIDE 14: AMAZON TIMESTREAM – ARCHITECTURE

### Complete Architecture Overview:

This slide shows the complete data flow architecture for Amazon Timestream,
demonstrating how data flows from sources through processing to visualization.

### Data Sources (Left Side):

1. AWS IoT
   - IoT devices send data
   - Through Lambda function
   - Into Timestream

2. KINESIS DATA STREAMS
   - Streaming data
   - Via Lambda processing
   - Real-time ingestion

3. PROMETHEUS
   - Metrics collection
   - Direct integration
   - Infrastructure monitoring

4. TELEGRAF
   - Agent-based collection
   - Multiple input plugins
   - System metrics

5. KINESIS DATA STREAMS + MSK + FLINK
   - Complex streaming architecture
   - Kinesis Data Analytics for Apache Flink
   - Real-time transformations

### Processing (Center):

LAMBDA:
- Processes incoming data
- Transforms and validates
- Writes to Timestream

AMAZON TIMESTREAM:
- Stores time-series data
- Memory tier (hot data)
- Magnetic tier (cold data)
- Automatic tiering

### Consumers (Right Side):

1. AMAZON QUICKSIGHT
   - Business intelligence
   - Dashboards
   - Reports

2. AMAZON SAGEMAKER
   - Machine learning
   - Anomaly detection
   - Forecasting

3. GRAFANA
   - Operational dashboards
   - Real-time visualization
   - Alerting

4. ANY JDBC CONNECTION
   - Standard database connectivity
   - Third-party tools
   - Custom applications

### Architecture Diagram:

